Subject: [PATCH 0/3] drm/bridge: sii902x: Convert to DRM_BRIDGE_OP_HDMI with D3 Cold PM

Convert the SiI9022 HDMI bridge driver to the modern DRM_BRIDGE_OP_HDMI
and DRM_BRIDGE_OP_HDMI_AUDIO framework and add D3 Cold power management
via DRM atomic callbacks.

Patch 1 extracts three helper functions used inline in the driver with
no functional change. Patch 2 performs the framework conversion. Patch 3
adds D3 Cold power management.

Backwards compatibility with existing DTS bindings is preserved: the
legacy hdmi-codec platform device is kept for boards using
sound-dai = <&sii9022> in simple-audio-card or audio-graph-card nodes.
It is unregistered only when the display controller uses
DRM_BRIDGE_ATTACH_NO_CONNECTOR (the modern path), where the framework
creates its own audio codec device.

Tested on AM62P5-SK with HDMI display and audio. Tested display output,
HDMI audio playback, hotplug detection, and suspend/resume with D3 Cold
entry and exit.

